[SN]TITLE[SN]
Catalans Dragons centre Krisnan Inu gets three-game ban

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Catalans Dragons centre Krisnan Inu will miss the next three Super League games after being banned by the Rugby Football League's disciplinary panel.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Inu was punished for a dangerous throw on Huddersfield prop Eorl Crabtree.
Huddersfield centre Joe Wardle and Castleford forward Matt Cook will miss their side's next two games.
Wardle was sent off against the Dragons after a high tackle on Remi Casty, while Cook admitted a dangerous tackle on Warrington hooker Brad Dwyer.
Wardle will miss his side's trip to Wakefield on Friday and Monday's home game against Salford, while Cook will sit out his club's derby against Leeds on Thursday as well as their trip to Catalans on Monday.
